      • parserFromFile

        public static InvisibleXmlParser parserFromFile(java.lang.String filename)
                                         throws java.io.IOException,
                                                java.net.URISyntaxException
        Construct a parser from an ixml grammar.

        This method assumes the input file is encoded in UTF-8. See parserFromFile(String, String).

        Parameters:
        filename - The grammar.
        Returns:
        A parser for the grammar.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file cannot be read or isn't UTF-8.
        java.net.URISyntaxException - if the filename cannot be transformed into a valid URI.
        IxmlException - if the input is not an ixml grammar
